English
instructions1aSTART
Interactive Stroop Effect Experiment

In this experiment you are required to say the color of the word, not what the word says. For example, for the words
instructions1aEND

instructions1bSTART
you should say "Blue, Red, Green". 

As soon as the words appear on your screen, read the list as fast as you can. 

When you have finished, press SPACE.
instructions1bEND

instructions2aSTART
Good work!

It took you 
instructions2aEND

instructions2bSTART
seconds to say the colors.  

Now let's continue with another list of words. Again, you should say the color of the word.

Press SPACE to continue.

When you have finished, press SPACE.
instructions2bEND


done1START
Well done. 


It took you 
done1END

done2START
seconds to say the second colors.  

The experiment is done,


Press space to end the experiment
